# Code owners for review routing.
#
# Ownership follows the change's blast radius, not its file type: anything that
# can alter how the repository builds, ships, or is gated belongs to Platform
# Admins; product behaviour belongs to Product Engineering.
#
# Dependency manifests are deliberately NOT owned by Platform Admins. This
# repository has no npm workspace. Python changes remain product-owned and are
# reviewed through the exact uv lockfile, Dependabot, the repository gates, and
# the manual advisory Snyk scan described in README.md.
#
# NOTE: a team must have write access to this repository for GitHub to honour
# it here. Without that, these lines are silently ignored.

# Default owner — product behaviour.
*                           @city-of-baltimore/product-engineering

# Content-team routing. GitHub can only honor teams with repository access, so
# Innovation Lab content routes through Product Engineering while the PR
# template records approval from the named section owner.
/docs/about-us/our-teams/innovation-lab/        @city-of-baltimore/product-engineering
/docs/what-we-do/services/innovation-lab.md     @city-of-baltimore/product-engineering
/docs/what-we-do/services/cross-agency-delivery/ @city-of-baltimore/product-engineering @city-of-baltimore/citistat
/docs/about-us/our-teams/performance/           @city-of-baltimore/citistat
/docs/what-we-do/programs/citistat/             @city-of-baltimore/citistat
/docs/what-we-do/services/citywide-performance-management.md @city-of-baltimore/citistat

